      "comment_id" : 134994982,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "As Erwin Smout answered, optional is created to avoid null. Although this answer &quot;works&quot; but you are destroying the purpose of <code>Optional</code> if you return <code>null</code>. IMHO the better approach is to just write what should be done after <code>findFirst()</code> is done, instead of returning the actual value."
