    "question_id" : 38725445,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>...findFirst().orElse(null);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Returns the value if present, otherwise returns <code>null</code>. The documentation <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Optional.html#orElse-T-\" rel=\"noreferrer\">says</a> that the passed parameter may be <code>null</code> (what is forbidden for <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Optional.html#orElseGet-java.util.function.Supplier-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>orElseGet</code></a> and <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Optional.html#orElseThrow-java.util.function.Supplier-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>orElseThrow</code></a>).</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 10444205,
      "reputation" : 1651,
      "user_id" : 7699822,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/YiTiI.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Yakup Ad",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7699822/yakup-ad"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
