  "title" : "&#39;Optional.get()&#39; without &#39;isPresent()&#39; check",
  "body" : "<p>I have the following search code in Java:</p>\n<pre><code>return getTableViewController().getMe().getColumns().stream()\n    .filter($ -&gt; Database.equalsColumnName($.getId(), columnId))\n    .findFirst()\n    .get();\n</code></pre>\n<p>I was wishing to find column by name and return first one found.</p>\n<p>I understand there is a case when nothing found and it should be processed, but how?</p>\n<p>Is this what it wants by this swearing:</p>\n<pre><code>'Optional.get()' without 'isPresent()' check\n</code></pre>\n<p>?</p>\n<p>How to fix? I wish to return <code>null</code> if nothing found.</p>\n<p><strong>UPDATE</strong></p>\n<p>Okay, okay, I just didn't realize, that <code>findFirst()</code> returns <code>Optional</code>.</p>\n"
}